SIMPLE: entailment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entailment
<hw>En*tail"ment</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
entailing or of giving, as an estate, and directing the mode of
descent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The condition of being entailed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A thing entailed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brutality as an hereditary <qex>entailment</qex> becomes an ever
weakening force.</q> <rj><qau>R. L. Dugdale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ental</ent>⟦br⟧
